extends layout

block content
    main.mx-auto.max-w-screen-lg.space-y-10.bg-white.p-12.rounded-lg.mt-24.shadow-sm
        section
            p.text-xl
                | This tool is optimizing svg file according to&nbsp;
                a(href='https://github.com/feathericons/feather' target='_blank' class='text-blue-600')
                    code.text-lg react-feather
                |  svg icon standards

            p.text-l.pt-4
                strong These are:
                ul.list-inside.list-disc.pl-4.pt-4.space-y-1
                    li Not using fill colors
                    li Stroke color as 'currentColor' (it allows coloring via css "color" attribute)
                    li Styled in 24x24 grid
                    li Stroke width set on 2
                    li Stroke linecap set on 'round'
                    li Stroke linejoin set on 'round'
                    li Nicely formatted html
                    li Using 'http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' standard
                    li Using ViewBox '0 0 24 24'

        section
            form(action='/optimize' method='post', enctype="multipart/form-data", class='bg-blue-50 p-8 rounded-lg')
                h3.text-xl.mb-4 Optimize SVG
                label(for='file-input') Select file and click optimize
                    em  (only '.svg' files allowed)
                div.mt-4.flex.items-center
                    input(
                        type='file'
                        accept='.svg'
                        name='icon'
                        required
                        id='file-input'
                    )
                    button(
                        type='submit'
                        class='bg-blue-500 p-2 text-white rounded-md ml-auto shadow-md hover:bg-blue-600'
                    ) Optimize
        section
            h4.text-xl How do I now that image is suitable for using as
                code.text-lg   feather-icon
                | ?
            ul.list-inside.list-disc.pl-4.pt-4.space-y-1
                li Icon is not cut from sides
                li Has no parts missing (Not using fill color)
                li Has nice stroke width of lines (sometimes bit different than original)

